<br>
1. What if he/she didn't do it? Innocent people get thrown in prison quite a bit. That question is the number one reason I don't believe in the death penalty.<br>
<br>
2. We are one of the last few industrialized nations that still use the death penalty. We're living in the stone age. The Salem Witch Trials are over, people.<br>
<br>
3. Saves money? Wrong. It costs more money to put someone to death than it does to keep them in prison for life.<br>
<br>
4. As stated above, I believe life imprisonment is a harsher punishment than death. I view death as the easy way out.<br>
<br>
People say the prisons are overcrowded and the standard of living sucks. Well, <b>dont' go there</b>! I know what it takes to actually get thrown in prison for a long period of time, and it takes some serious effort. You are truely given every chance under the sun to stay out.<br>
<br>
Do you want to cut down on prison overcrowding? Legalize Marijuana. <p><FONT SIZE=+1><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13102><B>Biggins Black: Assassin</B></a></FONT><BR>
