Notice how I'm going to calm down now hehe.<br>
<br>
My views on this, as with many other subjects of a philosiphical and social nature are what most people in this day and age would consider radical or communistic (when you think that, remember the quote 'i give food to the poor, and they call me a saint. I ask why the poor do not have food, and they call me a Communist.)<br>
So, I'll give you a little peak in to the nature of my perspectives on subjects such as these.<br>
I don't believe in black and white, in good and bad, in right and wrong. I believe that from birth human's know no different, they are social bodies waiting to be taught, to be shaped... Innocents, if you will.<br>
People don't do things for no reason, they are how they've been brought up, how the world has treated them. It's extremely scary the number of people that are clueless about the true power a messed up life can inflict upon people.<br>
So here we go:<br>
<br>
I'm against the death penalty. It could not be more wrong.<br>
For the practical reason, that people FOR it percieve death, murder, as such a brutal thing. However, they will inflict on the murderer, the exact same thing they are so 'rightfully' punishing them for. Do two wrongs make a right? I was always taught that they didn't. So, in essense, you are judging someone for taking a life against a persons will, only to commit the same act, and cover it with the label of justice. Advanced and civil societies SHOULD BE ABOVE THIS. It's primitive, it's brutal, and it's cold.<br>
<br>
Monsters. Human's aren't monsters, they are humans. We do thing for reasons, reacting to situations and past experiences. When a person commits a crime, murder, abuse etc, why don't we ask WHY? What can we do. Don't spill more blood, don't take more lives, let us be the bigger humanitarians, let us not banish our fellow humans, but help them. Sex offendors have had a history of abuse inflicted upon themselves. Murders are mental, brought up wrong, corrupt, mislead, provoked. People don't wake up one day and feel like a masacre. I'm sorry to burst your perfect black and white notions about everything.<br>
Reform, not destroy.<br>
But no, society now could never concieve of such a concept. 'Reform? Help? But, But.. isn't it cheaper to kill people? Because I mean, they're asking for it.'<br>
<br>
I'm going to deep here, I think I'll stop because I really can't explain my views clearly enough right now :P<br>
