ezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lets kill everyone who kills!</span><hr size=1> I find it utterly amazing that people talk about the death penalty as if we are talking about to use Taino's example... An abused woman who finally says enough and kills the man who has spent 30 years abusing her.  Sorry to disappoint your little example Taino.  But, these are not the people who tried under the death penalty.<br>
<br>
Those persons tried under the death penalty in <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> MOST</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> states are those who have commited crimes so heinous, as to be considered atrocities.  And those who are mass or serial murderers, killing usually FAR more than one person.<br>
<br>
We do have DNA evidence.  No it is not perfect, but it is damn near perfect.  And in most cases unless the match is 99% or close to it, then the person is usually acquitted.<br>
<br>
There was a time when it was actually a punishment to be sent to prison.  You gave up ALL rights when you were convicted.  Then, in steps the American Civil Liberties Union (whom I personally think should all be taken out and shot), and prisoners now have the right to vote, they have luxuries that most of the people who are working their asses off to pay for these lowlife scumbags, dont have and cant afford.<br>
<br>
We are paying through the nose for these scumbags to have cable, internet, a college education, what amounts to a health club.  When we cannot afford these things for ourselves.  Lets take ALL the luxuries away and make prison the punishment it was meant to be.  Or better yet how bout we spend all that money that they cost us, and use it to ship them to Sweden, and let the soft hearted, people like Halo reform their bad asses.<br>
<br>
I am sick and tired of pansy ass little whiners crying about how it is cruel and inhuman to not allow these <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> CRIMINALS</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to have the luxuries they so badly need.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> NEED MY ASS</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> No one NEEDS the luxuries these <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> CRIMINALS</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> have.  Hell I live without it and I havent even committed a crime but I'm forced to pay for their BAD ASS to sit there not doing jack.<br>
<br>
For the crimes that the death penalty is intended for, I am for it.  But I, like someone previously mentioned, do not think they should have unlimited Appeals.  One, two, fine.  But, not unlimited.<br>
<br>
But then I also happen to believe that punishment should be just that, punishment.  We have an entire society of &quot;no, no Jeffrey dont kick that little puppy&quot; children who have grown into people who have NO CONCEPT of being responsible for their actions. <p><HTML><BODY>
